---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Music - Felipe Triana">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-macondo mb-4">Music</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-16">Bridging Colombian heritage with Berlin's music scene</p>

    <!-- Cumbe Section -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-macondo mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold);">Cumbe</h2>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4 font-macondo" style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
        Colombian Traditional Music Ensemble · Berlin, Germany
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-12" style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
        Founded in 2022, Cumbe is my passion project that brings the rich sounds of Colombian traditional music
        to Berlin's diverse cultural landscape. We explore the rhythms and melodies that define Colombia's musical
        heritage—from the coastal gaita traditions to the Andean string ensembles.
      </p>

      <div class="ornamental-divider mb-12"></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-16">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-macondo text-xl mb-3 flex items-center" style="color: var(--color-gold);">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" style="color: var(--color-gold);">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"/>
            </svg>
            Gaita
          </h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
            Traditional Colombian flute from the coastal regions. A beautiful wind instrument with a haunting, melodic quality
            that's central to cumbia and other Colombian rhythms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-macondo text-xl mb-3 flex items-center" style="color: var(--color-gold);">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" style="color: var(--color-gold);" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"/>
            </svg>
            Bandola
          </h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
            Colombian string instrument from the Andean region. Part of the lute family, it produces bright, resonant tones
            perfect for bambucos and pasillos.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-macondo text-xl mb-3 flex items-center" style="color: var(--color-gold);">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" style="color: var(--color-gold);" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"/>
            </svg>
            Guitar
          </h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
            The universal language of music. I use classical and acoustic guitar techniques to complement and harmonize
            with traditional Colombian instruments.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-macondo text-xl mb-3 flex items-center" style="color: var(--color-gold);">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" style="color: var(--color-gold);" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"/>
            </svg>
            Music Harmony
          </h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
            Currently studying music theory and harmony to deepen my understanding of composition, arrangement,
            and the theoretical foundations of traditional Colombian music.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ornamental-divider mb-12"></div>

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-macondo mb-6" style="color: var(--color-gold);">Why Music Matters</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
        <p>
          Music and code share more than you might think. Both require precision, creativity, and an understanding
          of patterns. Just as I compose microservices into distributed systems, I compose melodies into harmonies.
        </p>
        <p>
          For me, Cumbe is about cultural preservation and exchange. Berlin gave me incredible opportunities in tech,
          and through music, I give back by sharing Colombia's cultural richness. Every performance is a conversation
          between two worlds I love.
        </p>
        <p>
          The discipline of learning instruments and music theory also makes me a better engineer. It teaches patience,
          practice, and the value of fundamentals—whether they're scales or design patterns.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ornamental-divider mb-12"></div>

    <!-- Connect -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-macondo mb-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">Interested in a collaboration?</h2>
      <p class="mb-6" style="color: var(--color-ink-light);">
        Whether you're organizing a cultural event, looking for Colombian music in Berlin, or just want to chat about music,
        I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors font-medium" style="background-color: var(--color-gold); color: var(--color-ink);">
        Get In Touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
